{"url": "https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/10/27/simon-cowell-rushed-hospital-accident-london-home/", "text": "Simon Cowell has been rushed to hospital in an ambulance after an accident in his London home.\n\nAccording to The Sun, he was stretchered out of his mansion in a neck brace after an ambulance was called at 8am this morning.\n\nThe music mogul, 58, allegedly fainted and fell down the stairs while fetching a cup of hot milk.\n\nHe was kept in hospital for tests before returning home in the afternoon.\n\nGiving a thumbs-up on his doorstep, he cast doubt about whether or not he would appear on The X Factor this weekend, the first live show of the series.\n\n\"I will be back but I don't know about tomorrow,\" he said.\n\nThe X Factor judge added: \"\"I fainted and fell down the stairs.\n\n\"I've got a bit of concussion. I feel better now.\"\n\nThe star was wearing grey jogging bottoms, a dark sweater and appeared to have a hospital tag around his left wrist.\n\nHe gave a quick thumbs up before walking through the door of his gated house, where a white Toyota sports car and white Audi were also parked on the drive.\n\nCowell had been at a Little Mix concert and had woken up at 6.45am, according to reports.\n\nHe was ill this summer, when he was forced to pull out of X Factor's London auditions. He also missed his own charity ball in June last year when he was struck down by flu.", "images": ["https://www.telegraph.co.uk/content/dam/generic/Matt-cartoon-255x206px-small.png", "https://www.telegraph.co.uk/content/dam/news/2022/03/15/TELEMMGLPICT000000249873510_trans_NvBQzQNjv4BqLf6XVudQ0d-fF3pHUPFzEAeAINc0hTrVyV1td0u1hTM.jpeg?imwidth=350", "https://www.telegraph.co.uk/content/dam/world-news/2022/03/15/TELEMMGLPICT000289557167_trans_NvBQzQNjv4BqOjwtMIBfBvsmIG0UzgZgYP4Xpit_DMGvdp2n7FDd82k.jpeg?imwidth=350", "https://www.telegraph.co.uk/content/dam/politics/2022/03/15/TELEMMGLPICT000288110703_trans_NvBQzQNjv4BqAGG6Q9kw2EHf5pW3wYN2voEnt97BhBUxp5YxaOlplSQ.jpeg?imwid